You can use an attachment in a rich embed without having to send the attachment separately.

1. Create an attachment using the [Attachment](https://discord.js.org/#/docs/main/stable/class/Attachment) class constructor. You can use a Buffer, local path, URL, or Stream to generate the file.

2. Construct your [RichEmbed](https://discord.js.org/#/docs/main/stable/class/RichEmbed) as usual. Attachments can be referred to within an embed with this syntax: `attachment://&lt;filename&gt;`.

3. By utilizing the `options` parameter of [`TextBasedChannel.send()`](https://discord.js.org/#/docs/main/stable/class/TextChannel?scrollTo=send), you can send both attachments *and* embeds.

Consider the following code which sends a rich embed with Discord&#39;s logo as the image...

```js
const { Attachment, RichEmbed } = require(&#39;discord.js&#39;);

const attachment = new Attachment(&#39;https://discordapp.com/assets/fc0b01fe10a0b8c602fb0106d8189d9b.png&#39;, &#39;Discord.png&#39;);
const files = [attachment];

const embed = new RichEmbed()
  .setColor(&#39;#7289DA&#39;)
  .setImage(&#39;attachment://Discord.png&#39;);

/* TextBasedChannel */.send({ embed, files })
  .catch(console.error);
```
